<TITLE> Over 100 arrests, 8,000 cases since start of traffic drive </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)Some 100 drivers have been arrested in eight days since Dhaka Metropolitan Police launched a special drive to restore traffic discipline in the city. Additional deputy commissioner (public relations) Walid Hossain said on Tuesday, from Dec 8 to 15, about 8,180 cases were filed against drivers and other vehicles under the Motor Vehicles Act. He added that over Tk 7.5 lakh was realised as fine for breach of traffic laws. Licences of 184 drivers were suspended for three months and 103 were arrested for violation of traffic laws and 157 vehicles were impounded. Vehicles were seized on charges of dangerous violations of traffic laws, running of old, unfit vehicles, fake licences, no licences, not abiding by traffic signals and under-age driving. From Dec 1 to 7, police launched publicity for vehicles to go by the three-lane system. Before that, from Nov 21 to 28, police experimentally controlled the traffic movement through automatic signalling. From Dec8, police cracked down on those not complying with signalling and three-lane systems.
